{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idab666088-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9110"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9110"},"text":"§ 9110.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Regular Air Force: strength in grade; general officers","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab666089-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9110/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Subject to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s526"},"text":"section 526 of this title","children":[],"tail":", the authorized strength of the Regular Air Force in general officers on the active-duty list is 75/10,000 of the authorized strength of the Regular Air Force in commissioned officers on the active-duty list. Of this authorized strength, not more than one-half may be in a regular grade above brigadier general."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab66608a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9110/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" When the application of subsection (a) results in a fraction, a fraction of one-half or more is counted as one, and a fraction of less than one-half is disregarded.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idab66608b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9110/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" General officers on the active-duty list of the Regular Air Force who are specifically authorized by law to hold a civil office under the United States, or an instrumentality thereof, are not counted in determining authorized strength under this section.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idab66608c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/500"},"text":"70A Stat. 500","children":[],"tail":", § 8210; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/861/s1/161"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–861, § 1(161)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-09-02"},"text":"Sept. 2, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/1514"},"text":"72 Stat. 1514","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/513/tV/s504/7"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–513, title V, § 504(7)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-12"},"text":"Dec. 12, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/2916"},"text":"94 Stat. 2916","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/190/dA/tX/s1061/a/23/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–190, div. A, title X, § 1061(a)(23)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-12-05"},"text":"Dec. 5, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/1473"},"text":"105 Stat. 1473","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 9110, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/dA/tVIII/s806/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, div. A, title VIII, § 806(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/1832"},"text":"132 Stat. 1832","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idab66608d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idab66608e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"ta